This paper is about attributed network embedding, which is a subfield of network analysis and machine learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning node representations from incomplete graphs, which is a problem that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. Based on the abstract and title, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which is specifically focused on network analysis. Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). These sub-categories are relevant because the paper proposes a new algorithm for learning node representations, which involves machine learning and data structures, and the algorithm is evaluated on real-world networks, which involves information retrieval and software engineering.
